      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE TEDEY (4) put the writing on the wall when chasing along the sprint lane for second two back then delivered here last week, finding the front before getting home by 1.4m. Draws a couple of spots wider but can go on with it. JOE LOU (8) rises in grade off the last-start Melton win but draws for a nice trail. Going well so could take the next step. There was plenty of merit in the latest performance of ALLWATFUNJINGLES (2) when coming from wider for second at Melton. There is a bit more depth here but he is well served by the low draw. SONNYBOY (3) has been freshened since finding winning form here last start, coming from one spot wider to score by 3.3m in a higher-graded race. Go well. KYVALLEY JENNY (1) has placed both times she has attempted this circuit and distance and should enjoy the favours from the ace draw.",
